cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with decision tree induction and the accuracy of decision trees on test data. It may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as decision trees are commonly used in AI applications. The paper also involves experiments and empirical investigation, which suggests it may belong to the sub-category of data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the use of a massively parallel computer suggests it may belong to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the investigation of factors affecting the accuracy of decision trees suggests it may belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
